1. RED PEPPER DIP Cut 3 cored and seeded red peppers into wide strips. Lay skin-side up on a baking sheet and grill until slightly charred. Toast 100g walnuts in a dry pan till lightly brown. Place peppers and nuts in a blender with 15ml (1 tbsp) pomegranate molasses, 15ml (1 tbsp) olive oil, 1 garlic clove, 5ml (1 tsp) ground cumin, a pinch of dried chilli flakes and a pinch of smoked paprika and pulse until chunky. Bruschetta with a trio of posh toppings2. PICKLED CARROTS Place a bunch of baby carrots (ideally the multicoloured heirloom ones) in a colander, sprinkle with 15ml (1 tbsp) sea salt flakes and set aside for 30 minutes. Rub well so the salt sinks in and place in a tall sterilised glass jar with a screwtop lid. Mix 300ml white wine vinegar, 375ml water and 5ml (1 tsp) runny honey and add to the jar along with 2.5ml (1/2 tsp) pink peppercorns. Screw on the lid and refrigerate until needed.3. PICKLED PRAWNS Place 1kg peeled poached prawns in a bowl with 5ml (1 tsp) salt, 250ml (1 cup) lime juice, 80ml ( cup) rice wine vinegar, 10ml (2 tsp) sugar, 1 halved lemon grass stalk, 2 chopped spring onions, 2 chopped green chillies, 125ml (1/2 cup) chopped fresh coriander and 60ml (4 tbsp) chopped fennel. Stir to combine, ensuring prawns are covered with liquid. Cover and refrigerate overnight.